main event: A round, white-orange object was seen as a flash in the sky near McChord AFB, Washington on November 16, 1956.
interesting points: The object was observed for 3-4 seconds, appearing slower than a meteor but faster than an aircraft.
The object was described as having a white-orange streamer.
The report concludes the sighting was possibly caused by a meteor.
An aircraft heading 182 degrees and 25 miles south of McChord AFB was noted in the report.
The sighting occurred at night with clear skies and scattered clouds.
photographs: Yes, the report indicates photos were taken, but no photos are included in the provided image.
